The paper discusses a general framework for online adaptation of optimization hyperparameters, which is a common topic in machine learning and optimization research. The experiments are conducted on a benchmark neural network, which suggests that the paper is likely to be relevant to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), computer vision (cs.CV), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
